						<summary>

						<p>On a broken slab lying in front of the Durgamma shrine.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1559 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated in <hi rend="bold">Siddhārthin,</hi> the other details being lost.</p>						

						<p>This damaged epigraph records a grant (details lost) by the Vipravinōdins to the <hi rend="italic">vidvanmahājanas</hi> of Saṅgāla <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vijayabhūpatipuram in Chiramāgāṇi in Gutti-rājya.</p>						

